\f2\b \cf0 Agentic AI Recommendation Service in FastAPI 
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 This service is a multi-agent travel concierge that 
\f2\b periodically 
\f1\b0 discovers great deals (scheduled scans), reasons about user needs in conversation, and turns those insights into actionable trip recommendations. It behaves less like a search box and more like a proactive teammate that plans, explains, and adapts. Use FastAPI for HTTP + 
\f2\b WebSockets 
\f1\b0 to push updates to the UI. (\cf3 FastAPI\cf0 ) \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs23 \cf0 \uc0\u9679  
\f1 Understands intent & constraints in natural language (e.g., \'93weekend in Tokyo under $900, pet-friendly, near public transit\'94). 
\f0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa8588\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \uc0\u9679  
\f1 Explains recommendations (tradeoffs, why this hotel over that one, key fees, cancellation rules) with short, template-based snippets. Watches for changes (price drops, sold-out risk) on a schedule and notifies the UI asynchronously over WebSockets. (\cf3 FastAPI\cf0 ) \

\f0 \uc0\u9679  
\f1 Finds and tags 
\f2\b flight + hotel 
\f1\b0 deals only (cars out-of-scope for MVP) using simple rules (e.g., price drop >15%, scarce inventory, limited-time promo). Builds coherent itineraries (bundles) that optimize for cost, convenience, and essential preferences. 
\f0 \
\uc0\u9679  
\f1 Answers questions about policies, logistics, and alternatives using fields present in the datasets (refundability, pets, breakfast, neighborhood). 
\f0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf0 Deals Agent (backend worker)
\f1\b0 : ingests small CSV/mock feeds on a schedule, detects & tags deals, and emits updates via websocket connection(feel free to use Kafka as well) 
\f0 \

\f2\b Concierge Agent (chat-facing)
\f1\b0 : understands user goals, composes simple flight+hotel bundles from cached deals, explains tradeoffs, and sets price/stock watches. Model requests/responses with Pydantic v2 and persist normalized entities with SQLModel (SQLite locally). (\cf3 Pydantic\cf0 ) \

\f2\b What the service does (at a glance) 
\f0\b0 \

\f2\b Primary user journeys Tell me what I should book 
\f1\b0 - User: \'93I\'92ve got Oct 25\'9627, SFO to anywhere warm, total budget $1,000 for two.\'94 - Outcome: The service proposes 2\'963 complete bundles with clear, comparable summaries (price, travel time, hotel neighborhood, cancellation terms), and a short \'93why this pick works for you.\'94 
\f0 \

\f2\b Refine without starting over 
\f1\b0 - User: \'93Make it pet-friendly and avoid red-eye flights.\'94 - Outcome: The service preserves earlier context, regenerates options that respect new constraints, and highlights what changed (e.g., \'93+ $38, earlier departure, 20-minute longer connection\'94). 
\f0 \

\f2\b Keep an eye on it 
\f1\b0 - User: \'93Track this Miami package; alert me if it dips below $850 or inventory drops under 5 rooms.\'94 - Outcome: 
\f0 \

\f2\b Decide with confidence - 
\f1\b0 User: \'93Is the Marriott rate actually good?\'94 
\f0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

